  • public class Instantiation
extends IIdentifier
    Value extension that represents the declaration of an instantiation node type. See decodeStatement(Node, String, Location, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static Instantiation decodeStatement(Node parent,
                                            java.lang.String statement,
                                            Location location,
                                            boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into an Instantiation instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Instantiations always begin with the 'new' keyword.
        Example inputs include:
        • new Person("Joe")
        • new Armadillo()
        • new String("asdf")
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a Instantiation instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a Instantiation.
